Abdomen brown to dark brown. Pygophore (
Figs. 6–7
): anterior margin of dorsal aperture rounded; inner projections subtriangular. In lateral view: dorsal margin slightly declivent posteriorly; with two faint protuberances posteroventrally. Parameres (
Figs. 8–9
): blade short and slightly curved; shank with an inner projection, with setae on upper margin and on basal portion of blade, outer projection with three long setae. Aedeagus (
Fig. 10
) without spines; vesica with two lobes, irregularly sclerotized; ejaculatory reservoir with small wings, vesica and conjunctiva slightly sclerotized distally.
